overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification and Statement of Work. The
  agent first conducted a thorough analysis of the existing codebase against
  these documents, identifying several critical missing features and areas for
  improvement, such as a tiredness severity scale, detection for specific sleep
  disorders like COMISA and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, weighted scoring for
  Excessive Daytime Sleepiness, and a more complete CSV data export. Following
  this review, the agent generated a detailed action plan. Subsequently, the
  agent systematically implemented all 8 items from the plan, updating types,
  validation schemas, UI components, and report generation logic. This included
  adding interactive elements for severity assessment, refining diagnostic
  algorithms, integrating external resource links, and ensuring all collected
  data was exportable. The process concluded with a successful implementation of
  all planned enhancements, significantly improving the questionnaire's
  diagnostic capabilities and data utility.
